    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Storage</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Storage on the DS10 target is presented through the Cypress CY82C693 southbridge IDE / ATAPI channels. This subsection covers creating and attaching disk and optical images and the per-bus device models. SCSI and the legacy buses are noted where their status is still to be confirmed.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Create Guest Disk Storage -- provision a disk image (manifest or mkdisk).</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Virtual Disk Images -- the raw image format and how a disk attaches.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Virtual CDROM -- the dqa0 optical device and ISO media.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">IDE Devices / ATAPI Devices (+ ISO-9660) -- the CY82C693 channels.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">SCSI Devices and the legacy buses (SDI / DSSI / ST506).</li>
    </list>
